commentary: Mohammad Saifuddin to Babar Azam, OUT yorker gets him on the toes on leg stump! Given and he's reviewed it immediately! Only doubt is whether this is sliding down leg. He was hit quite full and the review is showing three reds. He was struck in line with middle and leg shuffling across deep in the crease. Don't think he realized how far across he went. Very poor review. Seemed to be more that he did it because he was four away from a century more than because he thought it would be overturned.

commentary: Mohammad Amir to Soumya Sarkar, 1 run dropped! An almighty exhale from the Lord's crowd. In the channel on fourth stump on a good length, Soumya poked the bat out at it, healthy edge to Haris at first slip crouching right. commentary: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Shakib Al Hasan, OUT edged and taken! And Shakib Al Hasan's glorious World Cup campaign comes to an end. Tried to cut this square, but beaten by the extra pace, and he leaves to a huge roar from the Bangladesh fans. Seven half-centuries can you believe it. Take a bow, Shakib. Take a bow. Ending the campaign with 606 runs - the third most in a single men's World Cup edition (Both Sachin and Hayden played double-digit games though)

commentary: Shadab Khan to Mashrafe Mortaza, OUT clever by Shadab! Mashrafe had gotten into the habit of charging and this time telegraphed it too early. Shadab responded by dragging this back shorter and wider well outside off. Mashrafe not remotely close to the pitch trying to cut it as the ball comes to Sarfaraz just inside the wide guidelines outside off and he shuffles back to the stumps to take the bails off with Mashrafe's back foot a half meter short of getting back in.

commentary: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Mustafizur Rahman, OUT bouncer-yorker combo produces the best ever figures by a Pakistan bowler in a World Cup! Majority of the people in the ground and at home had to know it was coming. Mustafizur had to know it was coming. But this is just too good tailing into leg stump and Mustafizur is helpless trying to stab it out while backing away. What a show put on by the teenager!
